--Wait concepts
1)Why need to handle Waits ?  --> Synchronization issues
2)Why Thread.sleep not preferred for automation ?
 advantage: East to use
 Disadvantage : (Thread.sleep(5000))
    - if time is not sufficient then - get exception
    -if Element loaded before the wait time - But it still wait till the sleep time . This will affect performance
    - Each element wise - this comment will be used multiple times

 Note : That's why Webdriver waits mostly used in Automation

3)Types of waits in webDriver?
      -implicit Wait
      -Explicit Wait ,Fluent Wait
4) Types of exception mostly occur
     - NoSuchElementException -> Synchronization problem- locator currently not present in page(But locator is correct)
     -ElementNotFoundException -> Locator is wrong
---------------------------------------------------------
1)Implicit Wait(Global wait , One time declare-after d)
 comment: d.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(Duration.ofSeconds(#specify));
 - it should be declared after the driver instance and  one time declaration.

 Advantage :
  - Global wait -This wait is applicable to all statements till driver is alive(before driver is closed)
  - #Specify time is max time , so if element is already loaded before that it will excute - it won't
     wait for max time . and it goes to next line

Disadvantage :
  - NoSuchElementException might occur - if Element loading time take more then wait time .

